==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inmate
<hw>In"mate`</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n"m⟦amac⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>In</ets> + <ets>mate</ets> an associate.]</ety> <def>One who
lives in the same house or apartment with another; a fellow
lodger;</def> <specif>esp.,</specif> <def>one of the occupants of an
asylum, hospital, or prison;</def> <specif>by extension,</specif>
<def>one who occupies or lodges in any place or dwelling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So spake the enemy of mankind, inclos'd⟦br⟧
In serpent, <qex>inmate</qex> bad.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inmate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inmate
<hw>In"mate`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Admitted as a dweller; resident;
internal.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Inmate</xex>
guests.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inmeats</ent>⟦br⟧
